“This is Captain Kate, but you can call me Captain because it took me 19 years to earn this title.”Those are typically the first words that passengers hear booming over the speakers when they are aboard any cruise ship helmed by Capt.
Kate McCue.
“People don’t have a tendency to call men captains by their first name,” Captain McCue said on a recent phone call from her home in Las Vegas.
Captain McCue became the first American woman to captain a cruise ship in 2015, and commands the Celebrity Equinox — a 122,000-ton, 1041-foot ship in the Celebrity Cruises fleet.
My dad said I could be a cruise director or a captain or whatever I wanted.